@unnumbered What's New?


@newsTitle{August 27 Jul 2003, Site closed due to software patents}

The BEAST website joins the
@uref{http://swpat.ffii.org/group/demo/index.en.html,, online demonstration}
of the
@uref{http://www.ffii.org/,,Foundation for a Free Information Infrastructure}
against software patents and closes its front
page on August the 27th.

@newsTitle{Tuesday 22 Jul 2003, BEAST Realease [Velocity Edit]}

BEAST/BSE version 0.5.4 is available in the
@uref{beast-doc://download,,download section}.
@c here is the
@c @uref{http://gnomedesktop.org/article.php?sid=1182,,FootNotes announcement}.

Tarball:
@uref{http://beast.gtk.org/beast-ftp/v0.5/beast-0.5.4.tar.gz,, beast-0.5.4.tar.gz}
and patch:
@uref{http://beast.gtk.org/beast-ftp/v0.5/patch-beast-0.5.3-0.5.4.bz2,, patch-beast-0.5.3-0.5.4.bz2}.

Newly added features in this release involve a drum module, velocity-,
fine-tune- and control-event-editing in songs and support for post-processing
effects in songs.
The details are outlined in the
@uref{beast-doc://release-news,,NEWS section}.


@newsTitle{Friday 18 Jul 2003, BEAST RPM Packages}

After visiting the @beast talk at LinuxTag 2003,
@uref{mailto://gwaluga@@computerbraxas.de,,Gregor Waluga} 
wrote a small
@uref{http://linux.waluga.de/beast/BEAST-installation under-SuSE 82.txt,,HOWTO (english and german)}
about getting @beast to run under SuSE 8.2.
Assorted RPMs build by him are available from the
@uref{beast-doc://download,, Download section}.


@newsTitle{Thursday 10 Jul 2003, BEAST IRC Channel & LinuxTag 2003}

Stefan Westerfeld and Tim Janik are going to the
@uref{http://www.linuxtag.org/2003/en/index.html,,LinuxTag 2003}
this Weekend (11.-13. July). We'll probably hang out at the GNOME
and KDE booths if people want to catch us to talk about @beast{},
@uref{http://www.arts-project.org,,aRts} or
@uref{http://sfk.evilplan.org/csl/,,CSL}.

A
@uref{beast-doc://overview-de,, german paper accompanying the BEAST talk}
held at LinuxTag has been added to our
@uref{beast-doc://documentation,, Documentation section}.

If we're not hanging out at LinuxTag, you may also join us for a chat on
the @code{#beast} channel on the GimpNet IRC Network. The
@uref{beast-doc://contact,, Contact section}
has more details if you're not familiar with IRC yet.


